    • Package WorkLoadSet

      • Class WorkLoadSet.CoreSet

        class CoreSet extends Vector<Core> implements Serializable

        • Serialized Fields

          • alpha
            double alpha
          • beta
            double beta
          • coreSpeedSet
            CoreSpeedSet coreSpeedSet
          • currentPowerConsumption
            double currentPowerConsumption
          • currentSpeed
            double currentSpeed
          • gamma
            double gamma
          • groupID
            int groupID
          • hasPowerConsumptionFunction
            boolean hasPowerConsumptionFunction
          • isIdeal
            boolean isIdeal
            Whether this group uses an idealized power model.

            If true, the power is always computed via the analytical function alpha + beta * (speed/1000)^gamma (then scaled by 1000) regardless of per-speed lookup values. If false, the setPowerConsumption() method will prefer the analytical function only when coefficients have been provided; otherwise it will fall back to the CoreSpeedSet lookup.

          • parentProcessor
            Processor parentProcessor
